          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The SALAD(small angle large detector,",
                "consisting of a three-plane multiwire proportional",
                "chamber (MWPC) and a segmented scintillator hodoscope",
                " (PSH)-transmission delta-E and stopping E-detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The active area of the MWPC is 380*380-mm**2",
                "with exclusion of the central hole of 97.2-mm in",
                "diameter."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The PSH consists of 24 transmission detectors-",
                "delta-E strips(plastic scintillator BC-408 2-mm",
                "thick and 60-mm wide) and 24 stopping detectors-E slabs",
                " (plastic scintillator BC-400, 113-mm thick and 60-mm",
                " wide). The strips and slabs are arranged",
                " perpendicularly to one another.",
                " The thickness of the E-counters is sufficient to stop",
                " protons with  energies up to 130-MeV.",
                " The  energy  resolution  of  the  E-counters is about",
                " 5%.",
                " Within the acceptance of the SALAD detector",
                "  three-classes of the elastic scattering events can",
                "  be distinguished-",
                " -proton-deuteron coincidences when both particles are",
                "  fully identified,",
                " -proton-deuteron coincidences when deuterons have",
                "  energies too low to reach the stopping detector, i.e.",
                "  to be identified,",
                " -single deuterons."
              ]
            }
          ],
